{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@discardableResult"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"deriveColor"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"transform"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/Affine","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C36AffineV","text":"Affine"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"layerAlpha"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CGFloat","preciseIdentifier":"s:12CoreGraphics7CGFloatV"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"as"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"deriving"},{"kind":"text","text":": ("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/ColorDerivable","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C314ColorDerivableP","text":"ColorDerivable"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/ColorDerivable","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C314ColorDerivableP","text":"ColorDerivable"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.davidbjames.C3\/documentation\/C3\/Mutator","preciseIdentifier":"s:2C37MutatorV","text":"Mutator"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Uses the “ColorDerivable” interface for mutating colors."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Example: mutate.deriveColor { $0.lightened } takes the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"existing color (without needing to know what it is) and lighten it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Works for views, layers and also shape layers (via fill color)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Optionally provide transform or layer alpha to existing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Layer Addon (for color)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If Layer Addon does not exist the color will be converted"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a Layer Addon so that transform \/ alpha may be applied."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To ensure derived color is not “over-derived” (i.e. derived from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an already derived color) pass mutator option "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".idempotent"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If using idempotency, remember that setting the color explicitly"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via any other means (i.e. not derived), will reset the idempotency"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"flag thereby allowing further color derivation after. (CAVEAT: Setting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“backgroundColor” directly on a CALayer (not a Layer) will NOT reset"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"idempotency. Use “Layer” type or “Decoratable.color” setter instead.)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Randomization supported via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".randomColor"},{"type":"text","text":" option. Deviation is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"factor of 180º +\/- relative to the derived color."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example, a deviation of 0.1 would be 18º, causing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"final color to be a random hue between -18º and +18º from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the derived color, on the color wheel."},{"type":"text","t